  "slug": "what-does-admin-dread-say-about-me-journal",
  "title": "What Does Admin Dread Say About Me?",
  "subtitle": "Journal prompts for looking underneath the avoidance of financial paperwork",
  "excerpt": "Five journal prompts for examining what drives financial admin avoidance. The prompts move from the feeling of dread itself to what the avoidance is actually protecting.",
  "type": "PRACTICE",
  "sourceNotes": "Adapted from Day 53 of The Money Journal: 12 Weeks to Peace, Freedom & Overflow (Rebecca J Page, 2025, ISBN 9798276631448).",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Five journal prompts for looking underneath financial admin avoidance. The dread is usually protecting something specific: a fear of what the numbers say, an old story about capability, a general sense that money things are beyond you. These prompts ask that specific thing to identify itself. Set twenty minutes and write without stopping.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "New to journalling as practice? Read ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "journal prompts as practice",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "/mindset/journal-prompts-as-practice"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " first.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The practice",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Warm-up",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What is the financial task I've been avoiding longest?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Name it specifically. Not 'admin' but the actual item.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What does the avoidance feel like in my body?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where does it sit when you think about opening the form or the app? Describe the physical sensation.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Closer in",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What does the admin dread say about me, underneath the excuse?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Write what the avoidance is protecting. 'I'm afraid it will show that I'm bad with money.' 'I think I'll find something I can't fix.' Write it plainly.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Is that true?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Write the actual answer, then write what evidence you have on either side.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What is one admin task I could do in ten minutes today that would give me a sense of order?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Name the smallest possible task that would move the pile, not the whole pile.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this practice comes from",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Adapted from Day 53 of The Money Journal: 12 Weeks to Peace, Freedom & Overflow (Rebecca J Page, 2025).",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
